On October 24, 2007 it was announced that someone had shown the 2,3 TM to be universal. Links to the announcement and "proof" follow:

'nf
<a href=http://blog.wolfram.com/2007/10/the_prize_is_won_the_simplest.html?lid=title>announcement</a> (wolfram.com)

<a href=http://www.wolframscience.com/prizes/tm23/TM23Proof.pdf>proof</a> (wolframscience.com)

'fi
However, a few days later there was a dispute with the proof.  I am not sure of the current situation, but it doesn't seem to be resolved as of yet.  On one hand, there is a computer scientist making a theoretical argument then on the other there is Wolfram, et al. thumbing their noses at the guy.  I guess we'll see when and if the proof ever gets peer reviewed.

In the meantime, as good of a place as any to follow the saga is Wikipedia:

